column5: Lots of boats today.Maybe i fished it out this winter
You maybe did fish it out last winter,I know for sure I didn't put a dent in the population through the ice,lol,better yet I think you fished it out before I got there,you just left me the scraps
We are coming from winnipeg . I have met you at the tuesday cookout a couple of times and tried to book you a couple of times.
Miss the cookouts. Lol.hope to catch up.looks like a windy week as usuall.
It seems i have plenty of time this year.

Got out on Cedar Lake today.Wasnt going to go due to wind but decided to go at noon.Real windy at the lake.Was just going to cast for a few hours and take a little time out for walleye for supper.Seen a few fish today and ended up with a little one.lol.Caught a few pike and some walleye.Fun to get out even in bad conditions.Water temps down to 70F.Ill pick a better day next time.
The hurt continues, but keep it up!! Bill
Right on bill it's down right torture watching john have all the fun,although I'm sure it's hitting him in the wallet also,john better to see all of your pics than none,good job,rod

Fun to get out.And yes its expensive but not so bad.Yamaha is good on gas and dont have to go far.Nice to have free minnows .Those can add up if fishing is hot.Was windy everywhere yesterday.Terrova worked hard.Heading to Indian lake today with my wife.Better fishing there early and should be there already but slow getting going.No big deal. Weather looks good and hardly any wind.Going to launch at KC,s landing off the beach.It will be a nice adventure seeing some diff water.
Looks like you had some fun, nice fish.
I will be at northen lights for a week starting this saturday. Hope to see a few friedly faces. Will trade beverages for advice lol...
Hope to catch up.I most luckly will show up there at some time.iam headed to sioux lookout monday for a few days.

Fished on indian lake today.might have got there late as there was a zero bite on walleye.???.Hope you guys are happy lol.had a couple of lakers chase the lure but no hookups there either and cast a bit and only thing chasing the lures were smallies.lol.So you wanted scenery Bill thats all we got today. But wife enjoyed the ride and the swimming and the game of horse shoes back at KC landing.
Big muskie where are you coming from
John maybe there were a cpl of boats on Indian lake the day before you got there and fished the lake out
